t of malnutrition, liver disease_\nrenal\ndisease\nLiver disease: Serum transferrin variable; with acute viral hepatitis, high along with serum iron and ferritin. With chronic liver disease (eg, cirrhosis) , transferrin may be low. Patients whof\nhave cirrhosis and portacaval shunting have saturated TIBC/transferrin as well as high ferritin .\n***\nEnd Of Report\n*xx\nDr Pratap Patil\nDr. Saumya Gupta\nDr Balraj Raj\nMD (Patholoav)\nMD DNB\nPathologist\nAlumnus PGIMER;\n(M.DMBBS)\nChandigarh\nPowered by:\nBIOGENE LABS\nCENTRALISED LAB:\nugldL\npgldL\npRai",
